<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-71-0923 </DOCNO><TEXT>Reviews planned renewable energy source development in the United Kingdom- windpower, wave power, pumped storage schemes and geothermal energy- which could supply only a fraction of the country's energy needs. Discussesthe work of British Coal's Opencast Executive which in 1986-87 made aprofit for the thirty fifth year in succession, in terms of the lightin which surface mining operations are viewed by the planners, who wishto consign them to already derelict areas. Complains about the attitudeof the Royal Town Planning Institute towards portraying the facts aboutBritish Coal's successes in opencast mining and land restoration in itspublications.</TEXT></DOC>